Ubuntu 14.04:
0. Copy the project to the OS.
1. Update local package index (sudo apt-get update)
2. Update OS for security (sudo apt-get upgrade)
3. [SEE OPTIONAL #1] (Only applies to VMs, extra features for development by improving UI)
4. Install node (sudo apt-get install nodejs)
5. Link "node" to nodejs (sudo ln -s /usr/bin/nodejs /usr/bin/node)
6. Install npm (sudo apt-get install npm)
7. Goto the project directory and install packages (npm install)
8. Install MongoDB
	a. sudo apt-key adv --keyserver hkp://keyserver.ubuntu.com:80 --recv 7F0CEB10
	b. echo "deb http://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu trusty/mongodb-org/3.0 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-3.0.list
	c. sudo apt-get update
	d. sudo apt-get install -y mongodb-org
	e. In project: sudo mkdir database/data and database/logs
	g. Run (sudo chown -R "nameOfUser" /home/node/Desktop/MTG_Detect/database/data (OR try: Use chmod 777))
	h. Run (sudo chown -R "nameOfUser" /home/node/Desktop/MTG_Detect/database/logs (OR try: Use chmod 777))
	i. configure mongodb (found in /etc/mongod.conf) (point db to project directory /database/data and logs to /database/logs)

==========[Mongo Notes]==========
## The MongoDB instance stores its data files in /var/lib/mongodb 
## and its log files in /var/log/mongodb by default, and runs using 
## the mongodb user account. You can specify alternate log and data 
## file directories in /etc/mongod.conf.
## If you change the user that runs the MongoDB process, you must modify 
## the access control rights to the /var/lib/mongodb and /var/log/mongodb 
## directories to give this user access to these directories.
## SEE https://docs.mongodb.org/getting-started/node/client/ for info on connecting to db.

9. Start mongodb (mongod --config /etc/mongod.conf)
	a. To start: (sudo service mongod start) //Not relevent atm
	b. To stop: (sudo service mongod stop) //Not relevent atm
	c. to Restart (sudo service mongod restart) //Not relevent atm

10. Deploy Application! Woot!

